			Senior Advisory Director of The Goldman Sachs Group, Inc., an investment banking
           firm, since April 2001; Director of The Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. from 1999 to
           2001; Senior Chairman and Limited Partner of Goldman, Sachs & Co. from 1990 to
           1999; Senior Partner and Chairman of the Management Committee of The Goldman
           Sachs Group, L.P. and its principal affiliate, Goldman, Sachs & Co. until 1990;
           Investment banker with Goldman, Sachs & Co. since 1950. Director of Providian
           Financial Corporation and Tricon Global Restaurants. Member of The Business
           Council. B.A., Princeton University; M.B.A., Harvard University.

		
Source: Knight-Ridder, Inc. on 03/22/2002
		
	

 
 






